Software Developer
Lexington, MA
3+ years of work
US Citizens ONLY/ Secret Clearance preferred
Description:
A Software Developer is required to contribute to analyses across a broad range of issues central to the survivability of advanced air vehicles against modern air defenses. The scope of analyses will range from high-fidelity one-vs-one platform engagements to large networked force-on-force simulations.
The position responsibilities include:
Development and exercising of air defense sensor detection/tracking, command/control and mission planning software tools within a modern, object-oriented, modular architecture
Integration of system analysis and threat modeling into existing modeling capabilities
Surveying and capturing recent intelligence data to improve modeling data quality and validity
Assist in the preparation of PowerPoint and/or technical reports to convey findings to both internal and external audiences
Author clear and thorough documentation of all modified or developed capabilities
Education:
The group is seeking a candidate with a BS/BA in Physics, Engineering, Applied Math or Computer Science. Candidates with a relevant advanced degree will be given preference.
Required:
Strong academic or professional background in software development to include experience working with code of varying degrees of maturity
Proficiency in MATLAB, an object-oriented programing language (e.g., C++ or Python) and shell scripting
Familiarity with undergraduate engineering level introductory physics (Mechanics and Electricity/Optics) and associated mathematics
Experience running physics-based software and performing subsequent data analysis to reveal an understanding of underlying phenomena
Preferred:
Previous experience with air defense sensor, detection/tracking, command/control or mission planning model development and/or testing
Comfortable operating in both Linux and Windows environments, to include Virtual Machines
Familiarity with verification and validation of simulation models
Background in data visualization and display toolkits/methodologies
Excellent communication skills
Candidates with relevant professional experience will be given preference
An ability to take guidance and work within a small team, while working independently to achieve individual goals. Must be able to prioritize and handle multiple tasks. Self-motivated with demonstrated ability to excel under limited guidance
THIRD PARTY AGENCIES, SUBCONTRACTORS, AND RECRUITERS NEED NOT APPLY. Applicants received from firms will not be considered. Subcontracting is not available for this position.

FPGA Firmware Engineer

US Citizen ONLY / Secret Clearance preferred
Canonsburg, PA
6 months to hire

Seeking a mid-level electrical/computer engineer to develop, integrate, test, and support custom FPGA firmware within the Torpedo Systems Group (TSG). The TSG designs, develops, demonstrates, produces, assembles, tests and delivers torpedo SONAR arrays and electronic assemblies. The TSG team works with the Navy, internal production staff and the representatives from other companies to advance torpedo performance and lower production costs.
Job Duties
Be part of a team comprised of design, system engineering, and electrical engineering to develop embedded systems. Duties include:
architect, design, and document FPGA firmware hierarchies, components, interfaces, and data flows
develop firmware in accordance with detailed designs descriptions
simulate and test firmware components in preparation for integration
define FPGA timing, pinout, and placement constraints
review synthesis and timing reports, address issues
integrate and test firmware on target hardware
identify necessary schematic updates and hardware reworks to support design
utilize FPGA tools and laboratory equipment for integration and debug
document failures, identify root causes, implement fixes, and verify changes
maintain configuration management documentation for the FPGA design
Skills
Candidate must have:
experience implementing FPGA firmware including custom VHDL components containing state machines, synchronous/asynchronous logic, processes, and external interfaces
understanding of the underlying FPGA fabric the firmware utilizes
experience working across cross-clock boundaries
familiarity with Xilinx (AMD) and/or Altera (Intel) compiler, programming, and debug tools
experience reviewing schematics, parts lists, and re-work documentation
methodical problem-solving skills
motivation to independently research and resolve issues
strong written and oral communication skills
Candidates should have:
familiarity with floor planning and timing optimizations
Candidates with the following skills would be a plus:
working knowledge of standard network protocols (e.g., IPv4, UDP, TCP/IP)
implementing custom digital signal processing filters
Education/Experience
BS in Computer Engineering, Electrical Engineering, or similar degree
5+ years of engineering experience required
THIRD PARTY AGENCIES, SUBCONTRACTORS, AND RECRUITERS NEED NOT APPLY. Applicants received from firms will not be considered. Subcontracting is not available for this position.

Title: Mobile Test Engineer
Location: Omaha, NE work is on site. Candidates must be local.

Job Description:
We are looking to hire a results-driven Mobile test engineer to analyze, troubleshoot, and optimize Mobile products for our clients. In this role, you will be evaluating mobile devices, testing live applications, and troubleshooting updates, among other duties.
To ensure success as a Mobile test engineer, you should be able to test mobile products across multiple platforms including web applications, iOS, and Android. Ultimately, a top-notch Mobile test engineer should be able to work on various coding programs such as HTML and JAVA and display a solid knowledge of Mobile operating systems.


Mobile Test Engineer Responsibilities:
Testing Mobile devices to ensure their configuration, operation, and capabilities work efficiently.
Working with device manufacturers, product managers, and development teams to test and optimize mobile products.
Developing automated test scripts and frameworks for improved Mobile app performance.
Working with a variety of databases and coding programs, such as Objective-C, Java, HTML, as well as XML and JSON feeds.
Updating operating systems, specifically iOS, Android,
Producing clear and concise test reports and releasing notes to co-workers when needed.
Providing feedback to development teams on technical, troubleshooting, or operational issues.
Assisting with the configuration of test environments.
Suggesting new processes and policies to improve mobile development techniques.
 
Skillset / Experience:
Basic Qualifications for Consideration:
5 years experience testing Mobile/WEB application testing and development applications
Experience using SQL for test data creation and verification
Experience with test case development and execution tools such as Jira Test Management, qTest, or other
Working knowledge of mobile operating systems such as iOS and Android.
Drives continuous improvement through all processes, including but not limited to, team standards, test planning, resourcing and test execution, as well as debugging, metric collection, and reporting.
Bachelor's in engineering, computer science, computer engineering, information technology, or a similar degree.
Must be US citizen or Green Card holder and will need to pass a US Government background check.
Experience in developing automated test scripts.
Experience to automation with Opium & Selenium Tools
Ability to develop software applications using programming or scripting languages such as Java and HTML.
Experience in using configuration management or version control tools.
Strong communication and interpersonal skills.
Ability to meet challenging deadlines and work in a fast-paced environment.

Preferred Skills, Experience, and Education:
Bachelors Degree or equivalent work experience and/or Certifications.
Knowledge of Opium & Selenium with automation
Knowledge of Jira, SharePoint, Workday and or corporate based type applications.
Knowledge of reporting tools such as Microsoft BI, Jira dashboards, Excel pivot tables, etc.
 
Our benefits package includes: 
Comprehensive medical benefits
Competitive pay, 401(k)
Retirement plan
…and much more!

We are seeking an experienced Senior Reliability Engineer to lead our efforts in ensuring the reliability and durability of our products. The ideal candidate will have at least 10 years of experience in reliability engineering, including experience with automotive standards including AECQ, making component reliability estimates, component lifetime estimates, experience with JEDEC and ISO standards, lifetime behavior modeling, experience qualifying semiconductors including ASIC, failure analysis, DFMEA, and PFMEA.

Bachelor's or Master's degree in Electrical Engineering, Mechanical Engineering, or related field.

Strong understanding of industry standards and regulations related to reliability testing and analysis.
Excellent problem-solving and analytical skills.
Strong communication skills and the ability to work effectively in a cross-functional team environment.
Experience with reliability software tools, such as Weibull++ and ALTA, is preferred.
Certification as a Reliability Engineer (CRE) or equivalent is a plus.
Responsibilities:

Develop and implement reliability test plans and procedures in accordance with industry standards and customer requirements.
Conduct reliability analysis and modeling, including component lifetime estimates and lifetime behavior modeling.
Participate in product design reviews and provide feedback on design and process changes that may impact product reliability.
Work closely with cross-functional teams, including design, manufacturing, and quality, to ensure product reliability and customer satisfaction.
Conduct failure analysis and root cause investigations to determine the cause of failures and develop corrective actions.
Develop and maintain reliability test equipment and facilities.
Participate in the development of Design Failure Mode and Effects Analysis (DFMEA) and Process Failure Mode and Effects Analysis (PFMEA) documents.
Lead the qualification of new products, including ASICs, in accordance with industry standards and customer requirements.
Communicate reliability performance to customers and internal stakeholders.
Provide guidance and mentorship to junior engineers.

A Genesys Cloud Engineer is responsible for the development, deployment, and maintenance of the Genesys Cloud platform to ensure seamless communication between customers and businesses. This role requires technical expertise in cloud-based telephony, contact center solutions, and experience in implementing and integrating Genesys Cloud with third-party systems.
Key responsibilities of a Genesys Cloud Engineer may include:
Design and configure Genesys Cloud platform: The Genesys Cloud Engineer must have a deep understanding of the Genesys Cloud platform and its features to design and configure a solution that meets the requirements of the organization.
Integration with third-party systems: The Genesys Cloud Engineer should be able to integrate Genesys Cloud with other systems such as CRM, ERP, and other databases.
Troubleshoot issues: The Genesys Cloud Engineer should be able to troubleshoot issues that arise within the Genesys Cloud platform and provide timely solutions to ensure minimal downtime.
Manage Security: The Genesys Cloud Engineer must ensure that the security of the platform is maintained, and data is kept confidential.
Documentation: The Genesys Cloud Engineer should create detailed documentation of the solution design and configuration and make sure that all changes made to the system are appropriately documented.
Stay up-to-date with technology trends: The Genesys Cloud Engineer should stay up-to-date with technology trends and innovations in the industry and incorporate them into the system design where applicable.

Experience in the design, deployment, and configuration of Genesys Cloud platform
Familiarity with cloud-based telephony systems and contact center solutions
Experience with integrating Genesys Cloud with third-party systems
Strong troubleshooting skills and ability to resolve complex issues
Excellent communication skills to collaborate with stakeholders across the organization
